Now let me also verify if the new `shift` description is inconsistent with the pre-existing one at line 568.

The pre-existing doc at line 568: `@param shift the shift of the node (distanceFromRoot * BitPartitionSize)`
The new docs: `@param shift the current depth in the trie, measured in bit partitions from the root`

Since `shift = distanceFromRoot * BitPartitionSize`, shift is actually measured in **bits**, not in "bit partitions". Saying "measured in bit partitions" is inaccurate. The shift value at depth 0 is 0, at depth 1 is 5, at depth 2 is 10, etc. (with BitPartitionSize=5). So it's the depth *multiplied by* bit partition size, not the depth in bit partitions.

